smith.seaport

Class Thing

  • java.lang.Object
    • smith.seaport.Thing
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Thing>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Dock, Job, Person, SeaPort, Ship, World

    public class Thing
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Thing>
    The class Thing represents a instance of a Thing. Things are not directly instantiated by this program, but provide for polymorphism/inheritance in the code.

    Note: All Things posses a index name and parent(null allowed).

    Author:
    Hunter Smith
